+# PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
+
+- The fallback `preview_enabled=False` payload now preserves `approval_state`
+  and `requires_human_review`.
+- `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes `manual_review` to
+  `human_review_required` before building the preview payload, so the fallback
+  path matches the live-preview path.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`.
+
+- This thread describes the same reopened fallback preview regression.
+- No separate code change was applied beyond the fix referenced in `T-214-01`.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete.
+
+- The suggestion points at an outdated diff hunk.
+- I did not revive any legacy preview branch behavior on the current branch.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed in `tests/test_preview.py`.
+
+- Added a regression covering `preview_enabled=False` with
+  `approval_state="manual_review"` routed through `build_policy_preview(...)`.
+- The test asserts the normalized fallback payload keeps
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed in `docs/approval_policy.md`.
+
+- Updated the fallback payload example to include
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+- Removed the stale note that said the example still needed a future update.
