+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Applied the PR review remediation only in the allowed files:
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+- `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`
+- `artifacts/review/reply_draft.md`
+- `artifacts/review/remediation_report.md`
+
+No changes were made under `.github/review_export/`, to
+`artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, or to any other prohibited path.
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+This preserves the required shape of three actionable threads, one duplicate,
+and one obsolete suggestion tied to an outdated hunk.
+
+## Code and Docs Changes
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- Normalized `approval_state` inside `build_policy_preview(...)` before
+  delegating to `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Preserved `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback
+  `preview_enabled=False` payload.
+- Kept the live-preview payload behavior unchanged apart from sharing the same
+  `requires_human_review` computation.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Expanded fallback assertions for the direct preview payload.
+- Added a regression test for
+  `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+  to ensure the payload keeps
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback payload example to match the corrected payload.
+- Replaced the stale follow-up note with the current fallback behavior.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
+
+## Notes
+
+- `legacy_preview_hint` was not introduced.
+- The obsolete legacy-branch suggestion from `T-214-03` was intentionally not
+  applied.
